# 🔥 Outlier Detection using Autoencoder

## 📌 Overview

Built an unsupervised anomaly detection system using autoencoders.

✔ Reconstruction-based anomaly detection  
✔ No labels required  
✔ Threshold-based detection  

---

## 📂 Dataset

- Dataset: Breast Cancer Wisconsin Dataset (sklearn)
- Source: sklearn.datasets.load_breast_cancer()
- Samples: 569

### Classes:

Normal (Benign)  
Anomaly (Malignant)  

---

## ⚙️ Approach

### 1. Data Preprocessing

- Used only normal data for training  
- Standardized features  

### 2. Model Architecture

Input Layer  
Dense (16) + ReLU  
Dense (8) + ReLU  
Dense (4)  
Dense (8) + ReLU  
Dense (16) + ReLU  
Output Layer  

### 3. Detection Strategy

- Reconstruction error  
- Threshold tuning  

---

## 📊 Results

- ~65–90% detection depending on threshold  
- ~9× higher error for anomalies  

---

## 🧠 Key Insights

- Threshold controls detection performance  
- Strong separation between normal and anomalies  

---

## 🚀 How to Run

pip install tensorflow numpy matplotlib scikit-learn  

python anomaly_detection.py  

---

